libmicrohammer (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Testing infrastructure overhaul
  * Reorganized test suite: moved tests from src/ to tests/ directory
  * Achieved ~100% code coverage for parsers and top-level source files
  * Added code coverage support with lcov/gcov and --coverage build flag
  * Split parser tests into focused files under tests/parsers/
  * Added comprehensive tests for parsers, backends, allocators, and core library
  * Removed deprecated params backend
  * Moved build artifacts to build/ directory
  * Added test coverage documentation in DEVELOPMENT.md

 -- Mahmoud Elbasiouny <melbasiouny@riversideresearch.org>  Tue, 24 Nov 2025 16:00:00 -0500

libmicrohammer (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release of Microhammer, a slimmed-down subset of the Hammer parsing library.
  * Removed:
    - non-packrat backends
    - all language bindings
    - Windows/macOS support
    - Makefile build system
    - other non-essential files
  * Added / Improved:
    - improved documentation (consistent Doxygen for public API)
    - code style consistency (linting + formatting)
    - Debian packaging / build support

 -- Mahmoud Elbasiouny <melbasiouny@riversideresearch.org>  Tue, 04 Nov 2025 13:00:00 -0500
